1 Section 1. Chapter 422 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Department shall reimburse a member of the family of
4 a recipient of Medicaid described in subsection 2 for providing
5 personal care services that are covered by Medicaid to the
6 recipient.
7 2. Reimbursement is available under this section for personal
8 care services provided to a recipient of Medicaid who:
9 (a) Is less than 18 years of age;
10 (b) Is eligible under Medicaid to receive coverage for personal
11 care services; and
12 (c) Has been diagnosed with a disability or chronic illness that
13 renders the recipient unable to perform activities of daily living
14 without assistance.
15 3. The Department shall apply to the Secretary of Health and
16 Human Services for any waiver of federal law or apply for any
17 amendment of the State Plan for Medicaid that is necessary for
18 the Department to receive federal funding to reimburse a member
19 of the family of a recipient of Medicaid for providing to the
20 recipient personal care services that are covered by Medicaid.
21 4. As used in this section, “personal care services” means the
22 services described in NRS 449.1935.
